  "A homeowner has a $250,000 mortgage at 6.5%. They can refinance at 4.5% with $8,000 in closing costs, saving $330/month. The break-even period is approximately _____, and if they plan to stay 10 more years, the net savings would be:": "",
  "Break-even: 24 months; Net savings over 10 years: ~$31,600": "",
  "Break-even: 12 months; Net savings over 10 years: ~$45,000": "",
  "Break-even: 48 months; Net savings over 10 years: ~$20,000": "",
  "The refinance never makes financial sense": "",
  "Break-even: $8,000 / $330 = ~24 months. Total savings over 10 years: $330 x 120 = $39,600 minus $8,000 costs = $31,600 net savings. Since they plan to stay 10 years (well beyond the 24-month break-even), this refinance is clearly worthwhile.": "",
  "A car dealer offers two options on a $30,000 car: Option 1 is 0% APR financing for 60 months ($500/month). Option 2 is a $3,000 cash rebate (financed at 5% for 60 months: $27,000 loan at $509/month, total $30,540). Which option costs less?": "",
